Mott–Schottky analysis was performed in the dark using a 0.1 M KH2PO4 electrolyte (Fig. S4). As expected for an n-type semiconductor, both samples show positive slopes, and the flat-band potentials of the BiVO4 photoanodes prepared with and without NaCl are −0.036 and 0.177 V versus RHE, respectively. Equation 4 was used to calculate the carrier density of each sample.4Nd=2/eεε0d1/C2/dV-1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
